{"lemma":"مَهْجُور","slug":"مَهْجُور","root":"ه.ج.ر","root_slug":"ه-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ج-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَهْجُور","root":"هجر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40954"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"deserted, abandoned, forsaken"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"in disuse, archaic (describing a term that is not longer used)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of هَجَرَ (hajara, “to abandon”)."},"ipa":["/mah.d͡ʒuːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40954","headword_ar":"مَهْجُورٌ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cut off from friendly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse; forsaken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned: cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not spoken to."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.) In like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahojuwrFA","text_ar":"مَهْجُورًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the Kur, [xxv. 32,] signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaken, with the tongue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(B.) [But see what here follows.]       -A2-  Talk, or language,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered irrationally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolishly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliriously."},{"kind":"text","text":"It is related by Aboo-'Obeyd, on the authority of Ibráheem, that the words of the Kur,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a qawomiY A@t~axa*uwA h`*aA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ قَوْمِى ا@تَّخَذُوا هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@loquroA=na mahojuwrFA","text_ar":"ا@لْقُرْا=نَ مَهْجُورًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [xxv. 32,] mean,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily my people have made this Kur-án a thing of which they have said what is not true:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the sick man, when he talks irrationally or foolishly or deliriously, says what is not true: and the like is related on the authority of Mujáhid. (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}